00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,200
 If I have the gift of prophecy

575
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:17,700
 and can fathom all mysteries and all knowledge,

576
00:27:17,700 --> 00:27:19,240
 if I have faith that can move mountains,

577
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:22,360
 but not love, I am nothing.

578
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:24,840
 If I give all I possess to the poor

579
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,740
 and surrender my body to the flames,

580
00:27:26,740 --> 00:27:30,160
 but have not love, I gain nothing.

581
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:32,600
 It's fascinating what Paul does here.

582
00:27:32,600 --> 00:27:34,440
 He basically is talking to the Corinth church

583
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:36,880
 about their natural and spiritual gifts.

584
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:39,760
 But I think we can broaden it to us

585
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:43,360
 to think about humanity and how we express our humanity.

