00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:47,740
 Then the first verse, he basically says,

588
00:27:47,740 --> 00:27:49,960
 what if somebody was a really good speaker,

589
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:53,340
 a really good presenter, told a really great story,

590
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:56,180
 but if they did it without love, it's nothing.

591
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:59,240
 In the second one, he talks about wisdom and knowledge

592
00:27:59,240 --> 00:28:00,700
 and prophecy and understanding.

593
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:02,600
 It's like he's saying, hey, if you had someone

594
00:28:02,600 --> 00:28:06,120
 who did a great TED Talk and opened up a new way of thinking,

595
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:08,040
 gave you data to understand something,

596
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:10,280
 and you were like blown away by their intellect

597
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:13,160
 and their wonder and what they thought,

598
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:15,900
 but if they did that without love, it's nothing.

599
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:18,120
 Then in the third bucket, he says,

600
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:20,480
 what about you have someone who looks like they're loving,

601
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:21,760
 but they're not?

602
00:28:21,760 --> 00:28:22,760
 In other words, they're giving away.

603
00:28:22,760 --> 00:28:23,800
 They're giving away all their money.

604
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,040
 They're giving away all their time.

605
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:28,400
 They're loving in what looks like a sacrificial way,

606
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:31,120
 but they do it without sacrificial love.

607
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:33,240
 It is nothing.

608
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:35,720
 Which is Paul saying something

609
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,000
 very challenging to the church.

610
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:40,680
 He's saying, if you really want to be human,

611
00:28:40,680 --> 00:28:43,440
 if you wanna be the way that God has created you to be,

612
00:28:43,440 --> 00:28:45,160
 you can do all of these things

613
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:48,120
 that on the surface appear great human things.

614
00:28:48,120 --> 00:28:50,320
 Oh, the artist who tells an amazing story.

615
00:28:50,320 --> 00:28:52,960
 Oh, the incredibly smart person who knows it all.

616
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:55,520
 Oh, the person who's so generous with everything I have.

617
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:57,200
 You can do all of those things,

618
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:59,720
 but if you do them without love, here's what happens,

619
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:00,800
 and this is very important.

620
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:03,400
 He says, you are nothing.

621
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:06,580
 Notice, he does not say, your gift is nothing.

622
00:29:06,580 --> 00:29:09,600
 He doesn't say, hey, if you do all these great things

623
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:11,800
 without love, then the gift is worthless

624
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:13,080
 and nothing will happen.

625
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:15,280
 No, he says, you're worthless.

626
00:29:15,280 --> 00:29:16,980
 You have gained nothing.

627
00:29:16,980 --> 00:29:18,920
 You are nothing.

628
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:22,280
 I can get up here, and this challenges me deeply.

629
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:25,760
 I can get up here and do an amazing sermon

630
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:27,380
 and wow you with my oratory

631
00:29:27,380 --> 00:29:30,560
 and tell you incredible stories about nuns in Spain.

632
00:29:30,560 --> 00:29:35,000
 I can do all of this, and you can leave here going,

633
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,960
 that was a great message.

634
00:29:36,960 --> 00:29:39,880
 Wow, God spoke to me, and I learned something,

635
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:43,680
 which can happen, and I can do that without love,

636
00:29:43,680 --> 00:29:45,840
 and you can still go away being blessed,

637
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:47,620
 but I am nothing.

638
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:51,360
 This is the danger of what Paul's saying.

639
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:53,400
 He's saying we can have a world where it appears

640
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,800
 like there's all this great human wisdom,

641
00:29:55,800 --> 00:29:57,400
 all this great human stuff,

642
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:59,920
 but when it's done without agape,

643
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:04,840
 when it's done without sacrificial other-centered thinking,

644
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:07,480
 what it essentially will do is basically try

645
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:11,280
 to build yourself up rather than build anyone else up.

646
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:13,200
 See, I can preach the greatest sermon to you,

647
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:15,280
 but if I don't have love, I'm essentially trying

648
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,640
 to make myself great and not Christ great.

649
00:30:17,640 --> 00:30:21,160
 If I do it without love, I'm not actually thinking

650
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:23,560
 about you, I'm thinking about me.

651
00:30:23,560 --> 00:30:25,440
 I'm thinking about making sure this is the perfect sermon

652
00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:26,480
 that you're gonna love, and you're gonna go

653
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:27,520
 and tell all your friends, and more people

654
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:31,280
 will come to the vine, 'cause that's about me.

655
00:30:31,280 --> 00:30:32,520
 It's about my church.

656
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:35,280
 It's about this stuff here, and Paul's saying,

657
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:39,280
 when you do that, you are nothing,

658
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:41,840
 and Paul's saying, I don't want you to be nothing.

659
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:43,640
 I want you to be something.

660
00:30:43,640 --> 00:30:45,480
 I want you to be the very person

661
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:48,400
 that Christ has called you to be, who he's made you to be,

662
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:50,280
 so he's saying do those things, yes,

663
00:30:50,280 --> 00:30:54,400
 but do them from sacrificial, other-centered love,

664
00:30:54,400 --> 00:30:57,880
 and when you love like that, oh, the world changes,

665
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:00,520
 he's saying, when you love like that,

666
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:04,480
 things shift and change, but when you fail

667
00:31:04,480 --> 00:31:09,240
 as a human being to love agape ways,

668
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:13,240
 you will always end up imaging yourself to the world.

669
00:31:13,240 --> 00:31:17,160
 You will always end up filling the earth with your glory,

670
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:20,360
 and you will basically fail to become the person

671
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:21,720
 that you were called to be.

672
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:25,800
 It's really important that you hear that.

673
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:28,000
 When we fail to live as human beings

674
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:31,880
 from a place of agape love, we image ourself to the world,

675
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,840
 we fill the earth with our glory,

676
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:35,080
 and we fail to become the people

677
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,720
 that we were actually intended to be,

678
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:39,760
 and when that happens, that breaks the heart of God.

679
00:31:39,760 --> 00:31:45,080
 Agape is this incredible thought

680
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:49,440
 that actually I was designed to give everything to you

681
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:52,680
 so that you would be the best that you can be,

682
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:56,040
 trusting that you're gonna give everything to me

683
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:59,040
 so that I might become the best that I can be,

684
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:02,140
 and we do that because God has first loved us.

685
00:32:02,140 --> 00:32:04,080
 We're not trying to love sacrificially

686
00:32:04,080 --> 00:32:07,000
 in our own strength, we're not trying to love one another

687
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:10,040
 in our niceness and try to be a little bit better humans,

688
00:32:10,040 --> 00:32:13,800
 no, I've received a sacrificial love

689
00:32:13,800 --> 00:32:15,520
 that is founded in the cross of Christ,

690
00:32:15,520 --> 00:32:17,720
 and out of the overflow of gratitude,

691
00:32:17,720 --> 00:32:19,480
 out of the overflow of feeling that love

692
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,440
 and forgiveness of my sins for myself,

693
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:23,000
 I can now stand before others

694
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,380
 and want the very best for you

695
00:32:25,380 --> 00:32:27,800
 without thinking what's the very best for me.

696
00:32:27,800 --> 00:32:32,280
 This is radical because what Paul's essentially doing here

697
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:33,800
 is he's turning upside down,

698
00:32:33,800 --> 00:32:37,520
 common thinking about self-help and self-love.

699
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:40,920
 See, this world is like, hey, you need some more self-love.

700
00:32:40,920 --> 00:32:45,920
 Oh, get on that retreat, get away, prioritize yourself,

701
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:48,620
 put up more boundaries, make sure you're better,

702
00:32:48,620 --> 00:32:50,360
 make sure that you've got your time,

703
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,160
 make sure you're prioritizing you,

704
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:55,600
 love your truth, love yourself,

705
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,200
 and Paul's flipping it all upside down,

706
00:32:57,200 --> 00:33:01,080
 and he's saying you wanna know where self-love is?

707
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:03,540
 It's found in other-centered love.

708
00:33:03,540 --> 00:33:07,600
 You wanna know how to flourish yourself best?

709
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:09,440
 Give yourself away.

710
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:11,360
 You wanna know how to feel the best

711
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:12,560
 that you could ever feel?

712
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:16,160
 Love others like they're the center of your world.

713
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:19,280
 When you do that, something transcendent happens,

714
00:33:19,280 --> 00:33:21,240
 and you become fully alive.

715
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:25,080
 When a nun hitches up her habit and runs to a broken man,

716
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:27,200
 when I go over not understanding a word

717
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:28,560
 but lay a hand on his shoulder,

718
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:30,440
 not knowing anything about his story,

719
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:33,160
 I can feel the most alive that I have felt ever.

720
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:36,920
 When we truly agape in this world,

721
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:39,720
 we actually love ourselves,

722
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:44,440
 which is a very beautiful, complicated,

723
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:48,880
 incredibly deep theological, but also very practical thing,

724
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:51,320
 and it's this practical thing that Paul now turns to.

725
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:54,640
 Let me show you these words that he then speaks of,

726
00:33:54,640 --> 00:33:56,800
 and these are so famous to us, but again,

727
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:59,440
 try to follow along with this new thinking we have

728
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:02,240
 about sacrificial love for the other's benefit.

729
00:34:02,240 --> 00:34:05,560
 He says love is patient, love is kind.

730
00:34:05,560 --> 00:34:07,360
 It does not envy, it does not boast,

731
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:11,000
 it is not proud, it is not rude, it is not self-seeking,

732
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:14,560
 it is not easily angered, it keeps no record of wrongs.

733
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:18,040
 Love does not delight in evil, but rejoices with the truth.

734
00:34:18,040 --> 00:34:20,440
 It always protects, always trusts,

735
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:22,720
 always hopes, always perseveres.

736
00:34:22,720 --> 00:34:25,440
 It's really important you understand

737
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:29,200
 that what Paul's not doing here is trying to define love.

738
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:30,280
 Remember I said earlier at the start,

739
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,720
 it's hard for us to find the words that define love.

740
00:34:32,720 --> 00:34:34,240
 He's not trying to define love here.

741
00:34:34,240 --> 00:34:35,960
 What he's trying to say is you wanna know

742
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:39,400
 what a world looks like when people agape one another?

743
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,600
 You wanna know what it feels like for you

744
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:43,320
 when somebody agapes to you?

745
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:44,200
 You wanna know what it feels like

746
00:34:44,200 --> 00:34:46,600
 when you're able to give of someone else?

747
00:34:46,600 --> 00:34:48,440
 It feels like this, but also,

748
00:34:48,440 --> 00:34:51,580
 you wanna know what happens when we don't do those things

749
00:34:51,580 --> 00:34:54,560
 from a place of love, when we don't find love

750
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:57,420
 as the driving factor to the way in which we serve

751
00:34:57,420 --> 00:34:59,920
 and love one another, well, it then feels

752
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:02,920
 and seems and acts like this.

753
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:06,720
 So he's not trying to define some dictionary version of love.

754
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:09,960
 He's trying to paint a picture of how the world might be

755
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,400
 and give us the reason why the world

756
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:12,840
 isn't always like that.

757
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:15,880
 So he gives seven descriptors of positive outcomes

758
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,480
 and eight of negative.

759
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:18,640
 Look at this.

760
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:21,400
 What love is, patient, kind, truthful,

761
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:23,680
 protects, trusts, hopes, perseveres.

762
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:27,160
 What it isn't, envious, boastful, proud, rude,

763
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:29,680
 self-seeking, angry, shameful, evil.

764
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:32,320
 What he's essentially saying is this.

765
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:35,840
 If you do all the great things you can do as a human being,

766
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:38,720
 whether that's great speaking or great knowledge

767
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:41,880
 or great generosity, but you do it without love,

768
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:44,760
 here's what you're putting out in the world.

769
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:46,880
 You're putting out envious, boastful, proud, rude,

770
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:49,960
 self-seeking, angry, shameful, and essentially evil.

771
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,960
 That's what you're shaping in the world.

772
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:56,160
 But when you love with agape in the way

773
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:58,320
 that Christ has loved you and demonstrates

774
00:35:58,320 --> 00:36:00,640
 that love on the cross, well, here's what you put out

775
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:01,480
 in the world.

776
00:36:01,480 --> 00:36:02,320
 You're patient.

777
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:05,240
 You have long suffering with those that don't always get it

778
00:36:05,240 --> 00:36:08,800
 or kind of annoy you or kind of have hurt you.

779
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,440
 You have this kind, truthfulness to you.

780
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:13,720
 You protect, you trust, you hope, persevere.

781
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:16,960
 You wanna do all these things for others in the world.

782
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:20,800
 And Paul's not saying, hey, don't do these things,

783
00:36:20,800 --> 00:36:22,520
 try and do these things.

784
00:36:22,520 --> 00:36:25,120
 He's not saying, okay, the application of this sermon

785
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:28,000
 is just to try to be nicer this week, okay?

786
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,200
 If you could try to be nicer, that would go a long way.

787
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:31,600
 That's not what Paul's trying to say to his church.

788
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,120
 It's not what I'm trying to say to you this morning.

789
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:37,040
 This is not about finding within yourself more niceness.

790
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:41,240
 This is about realizing that the love that we receive

791
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,920
 through the Holy Spirit, remember, the fruit

792
00:36:42,920 --> 00:36:45,120
 of the Holy Spirit, first of all, is love.

793
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:47,360
 The love that we receive through the Holy Spirit,

794
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:50,280
 which is other-centered and sacrificial to us,

795
00:36:50,280 --> 00:36:54,600
 overflows within us and causes us to want to do anything

796
00:36:54,600 --> 00:36:57,800
 other than these things, causes us to want to serve

797
00:36:57,800 --> 00:37:00,440
 and to love and be kind and be grateful.

798
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:02,320
 It's not about trying to be nicer

799
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,280
 so I'm on the right side of the equation.

800
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:07,080
 It's about asking the Holy Spirit to create a fruit

801
00:37:07,080 --> 00:37:09,980
 of agape in me so that when a broken man walks

802
00:37:09,980 --> 00:37:13,240
 into a church, I'm the first one to run rather than the nun.

803
00:37:13,240 --> 00:37:15,960
 Come on, church.

804
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:19,700
 I got such a thing, she had such a thing in her

805
00:37:19,700 --> 00:37:22,160
 that when he stepped in, she went straight away

806
00:37:22,160 --> 00:37:23,400
 and left me behind.

807
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:24,240
 It hurt.

808
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:25,560
 No, it doesn't hurt, it doesn't hurt.

809
00:37:25,560 --> 00:37:26,560
 [congregation laughing]

810
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:28,440
 But I could tell the tour was over.

811
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:32,320
 But why wasn't I the first one to run?

812
00:37:32,320 --> 00:37:34,800
 Like, where is this agape-ness with me?

813
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:37,440
 When I look at these lists, if I'm honest with you,

814
00:37:37,440 --> 00:37:40,120
 I connect a little bit more on that side.

815
00:37:40,120 --> 00:37:44,960
 I realize that so often, my thinking is so self-centered

816
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,880
 and not other-centered.

817
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:48,960
 And I realize that if we could flip that around

818
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:52,080
 and begin to love in the only ways that Christ has loved us,

819
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:55,080
 which is always other-centered, never for his gain,

820
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:58,560
 but for ours, man, could you imagine what the world

821
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:02,040
 would be like if we could live like that?

822
00:38:02,040 --> 00:38:05,360
 See, it's that kind of love that enables you

823
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,560
 to turn the other cheek.

824
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:10,600
 It's that kind of love that enables you to embrace an enemy.

825
00:38:10,600 --> 00:38:14,600
 It's that kind of love that causes you to take your cloak off

826
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:16,400
 and give it to someone.

827
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:19,560
 It's that kind of love that actually asks you

828
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:20,680
 to repent of your sin.

829
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:25,640
 It's that kind of love that causes you to give to those

830
00:38:25,640 --> 00:38:27,000
 who could never repay you.

831
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:30,960
 It's that kind of love that causes you to get on your knees

832
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,760
 and to pray for this world.

833
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:37,360
 It's that kind of love that is other-centered focus

834
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:40,120
 that changes it all.

835
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:41,440
 And it's really important that you understand

836
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:44,800
 that this is not a soft love, no.

837
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:47,720
 Agape love is not the kind of love that just kind of

838
00:38:47,720 --> 00:38:50,000
 lies down and lets everything walk over it.

839
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,800
 It's not the kind of love that tolerates everything,

840
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:55,040
 that kind of allows everything to happen.

841
00:38:55,040 --> 00:38:59,000
 It's not the kind of love that denies yourself nothing.

842
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:01,440
 No, this kind of love, as Paul describes,

843
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:05,160
 it rejoices with the truth.

844
00:39:05,160 --> 00:39:08,640
 It does not delight, he says, with evil.

845
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:11,080
 So this is not a love that just basically says to the church,

846
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:12,880
 hey, just treat everybody how, you know, whatever,

847
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,680
 and just, you know, everything goes,

848
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:16,000
 and there's nothing bad in the world,

849
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:17,400
 and like, don't be mean to, you know,

850
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:19,600
 well, you shouldn't be mean to anyone, but you know.

851
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:23,080
 It's the kind of love that's not so soft and whimsical

852
00:39:23,080 --> 00:39:24,520
 that it's like, hey, anything goes,

853
00:39:24,520 --> 00:39:27,440
 just live your life and it's cool, be your truth.

854
00:39:27,440 --> 00:39:31,540
 No, it's the kind of love that rejoices with truth of God,

855
00:39:31,540 --> 00:39:34,660
 that rejoices with scripture and the promises of God,

856
00:39:34,660 --> 00:39:37,440
 that actually understands that and doesn't delight

857
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:40,040
 in the distortions of those things,

858
00:39:40,040 --> 00:39:43,640
 doesn't delight in evil, but rejoices with the truth.

859
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:46,480
 It's the kind of love that actually causes us to say,

860
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:49,480
 hey, I love you doesn't mean I accept everything

861
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:52,120
 that comes out of your mouth, everything that you do.

862
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:54,560
 My love of you, my agape of you,

863
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:57,820
 doesn't mean you can just act however you want against me.

864
00:39:57,820 --> 00:39:58,720
 Right?

865
00:39:58,720 --> 00:40:00,340
 It's not like a soft love.

866
00:40:00,340 --> 00:40:05,040
 It is a robust, beautiful, tough, run-through-the-church

867
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:07,320
 towards the broken kind of love

868
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:09,840
 that stands for the truth of God's word,

869
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:12,240
 even when that might come at a cost.

870
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:14,600
 Oh, a cost.

871
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:17,960
 Maybe agape love is sown more beautifully in cost

872
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:19,240
 than in anything else.

873
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:21,880
 And when we're found in those moments,

874
00:40:21,880 --> 00:40:23,400
 it changes everything for us.

875
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:26,480
 And I remember the great privilege I had

876
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:28,040
 of standing next to that man

877
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:32,160
 as he wept the horror of 20 years

878
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:35,120
 of being a homicide detective out of himself

879
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:37,920
 whilst he was being administered to by a nun,

880
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:40,440
 unadulterated agape love.

881
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:45,840
 The man just sat there for about half an hour

882
00:40:45,840 --> 00:40:47,280
 after we prayed for him, just on his own,

883
00:40:47,280 --> 00:40:49,760
 just weeping and gently being ministered to.

884
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:51,240
 The nun took me to the side.

885
00:40:51,240 --> 00:40:55,040
 And as she went to the side, she reached into her habit

886
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:56,860
 and she pulled out this.

887
00:40:56,860 --> 00:40:57,800
 She pulled out a pendant.

888
00:40:57,800 --> 00:41:00,280
 This is the exact pendant that she pulled out.

889
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:04,400
 And in Spanish, she explained something about this pendant

890
00:41:04,400 --> 00:41:05,600
 that I will never know.

891
00:41:05,600 --> 00:41:08,800
 (audience laughing)

892
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:11,480
 But apparently it was very important.

893
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,840
 And she placed it in my hand like this.

894
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:16,680
 And she clasped her hand over my hand.

895
00:41:16,680 --> 00:41:18,120
 And she said something in Spanish,

896
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:20,480
 which I assume was, I want you to take this

897
00:41:20,480 --> 00:41:23,080
 to remember this moment of love.

898
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:29,040
 As I left the church, here's what God was saying to me.

899
00:41:29,040 --> 00:41:31,960
 He was saying, Andrew, I've placed pendants of love

900
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:34,200
 around your neck over the years

901
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:36,680
 that I'm calling you to take off and give

902
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:37,520
 to those around you.

903
00:41:37,520 --> 00:41:38,360
 That's agape.

904
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:42,640
 And as I close our series on Advent,

905
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:45,800
 and as we prepare our hearts for Christmas on Wednesday,

906
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:47,800
 let me ask you the same thing.

907
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:51,440
 What pendants of love has Christ placed over you

908
00:41:51,440 --> 00:41:53,200
 over the last number of years

909
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:55,200
 that you might now be able to remove

910
00:41:55,200 --> 00:41:58,040
 and give outwardly towards the other?

911
00:41:58,040 --> 00:42:02,600
 Do that and the greatest of these remains.

912
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:05,280
 Can we pray?

913
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:06,100
 Let's pray.

914
00:42:06,100 --> 00:42:12,200
 Father, we are deeply grateful

915
00:42:14,760 --> 00:42:16,400
 that you love with agape love,

916
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:22,480
 other-centered, sacrificial, loving in its fullness.

917
00:42:22,480 --> 00:42:28,560
 Lord, we recognize that we have distorted such love

918
00:42:28,560 --> 00:42:32,440
 and that it's not just the world that distorts it,

919
00:42:32,440 --> 00:42:34,080
 but the church does at times too.

920
00:42:34,080 --> 00:42:38,920
 And we recognize, Lord, that often we live

921
00:42:38,920 --> 00:42:40,840
 in a lesser vision of love

922
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:45,880
 and that we act out a lesser vision of love.

923
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:49,560
 But we recognize that so often we can be selfish,

924
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:53,880
 self-centered, that even in pretending to be loving,

925
00:42:53,880 --> 00:42:56,080
 we're actually just looking after ourselves.

926
00:42:56,080 --> 00:43:00,520
 Father, I pray for anyone here this morning

927
00:43:00,520 --> 00:43:03,160
 where that might be part of their story,

928
00:43:03,160 --> 00:43:04,720
 that they would have the courage today

929
00:43:04,720 --> 00:43:05,880
 to bring that to you,

930
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:09,240
 that in your agape love,

931
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:12,840
 we would, out of your kindness, be led to repentance.

932
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:17,080
 Lord, I recognize also that there's people in this room

933
00:43:17,080 --> 00:43:18,760
 watching online in our overflow

934
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:21,320
 who have been hurt by broken love,

935
00:43:21,320 --> 00:43:25,680
 who somebody else's brokenness of love

936
00:43:25,680 --> 00:43:29,040
 has acted upon them in ways that has deeply hurt them.

937
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:34,440
 Father, I pray for anyone here where that's their story.

938
00:43:34,440 --> 00:43:38,080
 And because of how broken love has impacted them,

939
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:40,280
 they have been loving brokenly themselves.

940
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:44,000
 Father, we do know that we are able to love

941
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:45,040
 because you first loved us.

942
00:43:45,040 --> 00:43:47,480
 And I pray that if there's anyone in this room

943
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:48,720
 where that's a bit of their journey

944
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:50,800
 or a bit of their story right now,

945
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:53,200
 they've been broken and hurt by love

946
00:43:53,200 --> 00:43:56,160
 and they find that they're swept up in that story,

947
00:43:56,160 --> 00:43:58,840
 I wanna pray, Lord, that your Spirit,

948
00:43:58,840 --> 00:44:02,360
 which you have poured out in this time,

949
00:44:02,360 --> 00:44:03,760
 in this now but not yet time

950
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:06,120
 between your birth and your return,

951
00:44:06,120 --> 00:44:08,320
 I pray that that Spirit and the fruit

952
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:12,200
 of that Spirit of love, pure, unadulterated,

953
00:44:12,200 --> 00:44:16,000
 agape, sacrificial, selfless, other-scented love

954
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:17,320
 would fall on them,

955
00:44:17,320 --> 00:44:23,040
 would come up and be birthed within them for your glory.

956
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:26,360
 Lord, I pray for families

957
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:28,400
 that have been torn apart by broken love.

958
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:32,720
 Father, I pray for husbands and wives in this room,

959
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:36,080
 those that are struggling to love,

960
00:44:36,080 --> 00:44:39,120
 those that perhaps loved before

961
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:42,400
 but find themselves without it in this time,

962
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:47,280
 marriages that are strained and difficult.

963
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:52,680
 Lord, we don't downplay that, we don't brush over that.

964
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:55,360
 And Lord, we recognize that the only thing

965
00:44:55,360 --> 00:44:58,120
 that heals that kind of brokenness

966
00:44:58,120 --> 00:45:02,360
 is the kind of love that is seen on the cross of Christ

967
00:45:02,360 --> 00:45:03,880
 and a love that brings us once again

968
00:45:03,880 --> 00:45:07,280
 to the most natural state of what it is to be human.

969
00:45:07,280 --> 00:45:10,320
 Lord, I pray for marriages in this room

970
00:45:10,320 --> 00:45:14,520
 that you would restore agape love in the name of Jesus.

971
00:45:14,520 --> 00:45:16,920
 Lord, I pray for businesses and families.

972
00:45:16,920 --> 00:45:20,540
 I pray for relationships that have been strained.

973
00:45:20,540 --> 00:45:24,080
 Lord, we pray that we would be able to become a church

974
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:27,720
 that has received such agape love ourselves

975
00:45:27,720 --> 00:45:31,240
 that we cannot but help to move out in that love

976
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:35,120
 for the glory of Christ, imaging you to the world

977
00:45:35,120 --> 00:45:36,960
 and not ourselves.

978
00:45:36,960 --> 00:45:39,520
 Lord, as we come to celebrate your birth on Wednesday,

979
00:45:39,520 --> 00:45:44,520
 would it be this agapeness that would mark the Vine Church?

980
00:45:44,520 --> 00:45:46,760
 Would it mark us in the days ahead?

981
00:45:46,760 --> 00:45:49,520
 And would it mark us as we enter into 2025

982
00:45:49,520 --> 00:45:51,480
 and all the things that you have for us ahead?

983
00:45:51,480 --> 00:45:55,000
 Would we love in the way that you truly called us to love?

984
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:59,480
 And we give you glory for this, in Jesus' name.

985
00:46:01,120 --> 00:46:03,080
 Would you stand with me and we're going

986
00:46:03,080 --> 00:46:05,720
 to just respond together in a time of worship.

